    "body" : "<p>The is related but not exactly what you asked.  But I needed it and I can imagine others do to. \nSo I had the problem in Node.js where I wanted to split a reject into call into a log and reject for clarity</p>\n\n<p><code>reject(error)</code></p>\n\n<p>into </p>\n\n<p><code>appLogger.log(error, 'error')\n reject(error)\n</code></p>\n\n<p>In normal mode, I did find and replace </p>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p>Find: <code>reject(error)</code></p>\n  \n  <p>Replace: <code>appLogger.log(error, 'error')\\n reject(error)</code></p>\n</blockquote>\n\n<p>Then in regex mode I did a second find and replace:</p>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p>Find: <code>\\\\n</code></p>\n  \n  <p>Replace <code>\\n</code></p>\n</blockquote>\n"
